<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Top raid... maybe, yes. Top group? Nope, surely not. We are ok, but not 'top'. Top solo? WIth the recent patch... uhm nope. And then all of us are interested in soloing, but prefer grouping.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I was not aware that the recent patch nerfed our damage. Please show me how our solo damage has changed since yesterday. Also, please post some parses of a class doing more damage over the long term than wizard. Don't bother with 2 minutes of ranger TS or the 3 minutes of charmed pet damage from a mage/chanter before they get splattered. Read what I typed, I said we are the top DAMAGE class. Please site some examples showing we are not. I think it would be foolish to say that we are not the best overall damage class. We might get outdamaged in some specific situations, but as a whole we do more damage than any other class in general.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>About places where to quad kite. YOu said there were dozens. nope, not true. Well the recent exp range patch has to reveal, if some more zones are worth to call 'quaddable' as a level 65.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
and<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Where are these dozens of quaddable zones at 65?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Where did I say there are dozens of quaddable zones at 65? I seem to remember replying to a post that suggested I was out of touch since I am in the elemental planes. I specifically spoke of the wizard class as a whole, not as level 65.<br>
<br>
However, I will give you some ideas on where to quad at 65 for pretty good exp. Keep in mind that lvl 50 mobs are dark blue again so it really opens up a lot of possibilities. I will not list any zones that require flags or keys.<br>
<br>
Plane of Storm - frogs<br>
Plane of Valor - undead vassals, crystalline golems<br>
Plane of Nightmare - birds (lvl51-54), nettling wraith (55), spiders (51-55), nightstalkers (59-60)<br>
Plane of Disease - underbulks (55-57)<br>
Halls of Honor - entrance mobs, basement mobs<br>
Fungus grove - shadel bandits (51-53)<br>
The Grey - sun revenant (55)<br>
Maiden's Eye - goranga scout (56-59), mind burrower (52-56), reanimated drudge (49-55), bats (49-55), coterie (49-55)<br>
Katta Castellum - guards should be easier now that pathing works pretty well.<br>
Umbral Plains - everything in the zone is 50+. I never quadded there, but I know people who did.<br>
Crypt of Nadox - all of the mobs in the mines are 50+ and snareable. Scout around, plenty of room and mobs if you are good. I did it last night while camping for a Platinum disk. Still got some exp before the mob level change.<br>
<br>
There you go. 11 zones you can quad in at 65. It remains to be seen just how good the exp will be in some of the zones, but every one of those has plenty of dark blue to 65 mobs that are prime quad material. This does not even include mobs that are not snareable that can be full speed quadded in other zones, or quadding that can be done in zones if you are flagged. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=26850.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=26850.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=26850.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a> <b>4</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=26850.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=26850.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=26850.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=26850.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=26850.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  